byline.original: By NELSON D. SCHWARTZ and ERIC DASH

abstract: Bank revenue is expected to fall 4 percent in third quarter, slipping back to 2005 levels, with profits expected to be about those of late 2002; bank stocks have fallen as investors leave industry; banks are trying to recoup billions of dollars in lost revenue with fee increases, such as Bank of America's unpopular debit card fee.
snippet: Banks, the fulcrum of a huge protest downtown, may be about to prove disheartened investors right.
lead_paragraph: Banks, the fulcrum of a huge protest downtown, may be about to prove disheartened investors right.

headline.main: Banks Brace for Fallout on Earnings

headline.seo: Banks Brace for Bad News as Earnings Season Arrives
